1
00:00:12,350 --> 00:00:14,709
So why do you keep provoking them?

2
00:00:15,279 --> 00:00:17,320
They think you're the bad guy.

3
00:00:18,519 --> 00:00:20,889
I don't care what they think.

4
00:00:24,220 --> 00:00:26,630
The more I think about it,
the more baffled I get.

5
00:00:27,659 --> 00:00:30,630
There are plenty of seniors.
How dare they order you to protest?

6
00:00:31,260 --> 00:00:33,269
They're obviously trying
to dump it all on you...

7
00:00:33,270 --> 00:00:35,150
because they don't want
to be dragged to Namsan.

8
00:00:36,439 --> 00:00:37,840
It's my choice.

9
00:00:38,469 --> 00:00:40,170
No one put me up to it.

10
00:00:42,609 --> 00:00:45,209
Sure. Whatever, Mr. Fighter.

11
00:00:46,950 --> 00:00:49,649
Everything you do bothers me.

12
00:00:50,749 --> 00:00:53,190
And what's with this lame taste
in music?

13
00:00:54,749 --> 00:00:57,060
You told me to request a song
I wanted to listen to.

14
00:00:57,920 --> 00:00:59,660
Why must you nitpick
about everything?

15
00:01:00,429 --> 00:01:01,959
We really don't see eye to eye.

16
00:01:03,130 --> 00:01:05,230
You say that all the time.

17
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:07,469
Why did you team up with me then?

18
00:01:07,899 --> 00:01:09,500
What do you think?

19
00:01:10,869 --> 00:01:13,349
Probably because you couldn't find
anyone else to write lyrics.

20
00:01:13,940 --> 00:01:16,880
I'm sorry, but there are many people
who can do that.

21
00:01:17,709 --> 00:01:18,979
Then what?

22
00:01:19,979 --> 00:01:23,249
- Because I'm a nice person?
- You're saying that about yourself?

23
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:24,479
Have you gone mad?

24
00:01:26,949 --> 00:01:30,020
That's what everyone else says.
They say I'm nice.

25
00:01:30,819 --> 00:01:32,229
And that's why they all like me.

26
00:01:34,459 --> 00:01:35,699
My goodness.

27
00:01:39,970 --> 00:01:41,270
Kim Kyung Soo.

28
00:01:42,199 --> 00:01:43,740
Don't be delusional.

29
00:01:44,669 --> 00:01:46,569
You're not a good person.

30
00:02:04,220 --> 00:02:06,990
You punks.
Do you think you're on a picnic now?

31
00:02:07,630 --> 00:02:10,830
Hurry up! You're all so slow.

32
00:02:31,319 --> 00:02:33,220
Hee Tae, the ambulance is arriving.

33
00:02:33,419 --> 00:02:34,549
Oh, okay.

34
00:02:39,560 --> 00:02:44,130
(Episode 10,
Goodness, Hypocrisy, Utmost Effort)

35
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:48,698
The martial law army headquarters...

36
00:02:48,699 --> 00:02:50,768
Can't you write it properly?
What is this?

37
00:02:50,769 --> 00:02:52,009
Do you have an accurate count?

38
00:02:52,210 --> 00:02:53,940
Yes, I think so.

39
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:07,690
What are you doing here?

40
00:03:07,919 --> 00:03:09,819
I thought you moved to Seoul
to get married.

41
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:16,129
I'll just get the medical supplies
and leave.

42
00:03:16,130 --> 00:03:17,199
Don't mind me.

43
00:03:17,630 --> 00:03:21,329
Why? Did your father-in-law
send you here to spy on us?

44
00:03:22,269 --> 00:03:23,340
What?

45
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:24,698
Am I wrong?

46
00:03:24,699 --> 00:03:26,470
Are you the Grim Reaper
or something?

47
00:03:26,769 --> 00:03:29,440
Everyone who met up with you
has disappeared.

48
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:32,949
Did Hye Gun also go missing
after meeting up with you?

49
00:03:35,049 --> 00:03:36,850
It was me, not her.

50
00:03:39,549 --> 00:03:42,489
Hye Gun met with me
before he went missing.

51
00:03:42,789 --> 00:03:45,319
Does that make me
the Grim Reaper too?

52
00:03:45,690 --> 00:03:48,329
Why are you taking it out on her?

53
00:03:49,100 --> 00:03:50,529
That's because her fiance is...

54
00:03:50,530 --> 00:03:52,199
She moved out.

55
00:03:53,169 --> 00:03:54,199
What?

56
00:03:54,329 --> 00:03:57,639
She moved out.
Look at her. Can't you tell?

57
00:03:57,739 --> 00:04:01,109
Both she and I have been helping
the victims for days, nonstop.

58
00:04:02,139 --> 00:04:04,478
So don't waste your energy
attacking someone...

59
00:04:04,479 --> 00:04:06,279
who's working toward the same goal
as you are.

60
00:04:19,489 --> 00:04:22,499
Boo Yong, that thing...

61
00:04:23,059 --> 00:04:24,260
Did you finish it?

62
00:04:24,999 --> 00:04:28,700
What's with this handwriting?
Make the letters bigger.

63
00:04:30,869 --> 00:04:32,640
Keep your head down, please.

64
00:04:32,739 --> 00:04:35,368
- This will be quick.
- This is only his second day here,

65
00:04:35,369 --> 00:04:37,710
but he's better at intubation
than Dr. Song,

66
00:04:38,010 --> 00:04:39,478
who's been an intern
for half a year.

67
00:04:39,479 --> 00:04:41,308
He already got the hang of it.

68
00:04:41,309 --> 00:04:42,549
I know.

69
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:45,789
He passed the exam
with the highest score, you know.

70
00:04:45,950 --> 00:04:48,650
Don't blatantly stare at him.
Let's just take a quick glance.

71
00:05:02,299 --> 00:05:03,869
Does anyone have a moment to spare?

72
00:05:04,299 --> 00:05:06,470
Please go take care of Kim Duk Bae.

73
00:05:06,739 --> 00:05:08,779
Kim Duk Bae? The delirious patient?

74
00:05:08,780 --> 00:05:09,909
The one who beats up everyone?

75
00:05:09,910 --> 00:05:12,549
That's right.
He's just not getting better.

76
00:05:12,910 --> 00:05:14,478
Give him more sedatives.

77
00:05:14,479 --> 00:05:16,320
- And take this urinary bag...
- What?

78
00:05:16,979 --> 00:05:19,090
- Attach this urinary bag too.
- Goodness.

79
00:05:21,419 --> 00:05:22,460
Here.

80
00:05:27,890 --> 00:05:29,299
I'll do it.

81
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:31,799
Really?

82
00:05:38,970 --> 00:05:40,369
Myeong Hee, what are you doing?

83
00:05:40,970 --> 00:05:42,070
What?

84
00:05:42,179 --> 00:05:43,709
We have to admit the new patient.

85
00:05:43,710 --> 00:05:46,309
The ambulance is arriving now.
It's an emergency patient.

86
00:05:47,379 --> 00:05:48,379
We'll be right back.

87
00:05:50,049 --> 00:05:51,179
Wait...

88
00:05:53,220 --> 00:05:56,320
Clearly, he's already made himself
at home here.

89
00:05:57,460 --> 00:06:00,160
- No one's coming?
- I'm coming.

90
00:06:01,129 --> 00:06:04,229
How many times must I tell you?
Don't step in unless you're told to.

91
00:06:04,729 --> 00:06:06,329
Why would you volunteer
to do the difficult tasks?

92
00:06:06,330 --> 00:06:08,128
Why should that matter?

93
00:06:08,129 --> 00:06:09,869
I just want to do the things
that I can do.

94
00:06:11,539 --> 00:06:13,069
Does it mean other people...

95
00:06:13,070 --> 00:06:14,785
avoid it because
they don't know how to work?

96
00:06:14,809 --> 00:06:17,509
See? They keep forcing
everything on you...

97
00:06:17,510 --> 00:06:18,780
since they know you'll say yes.

98
00:06:19,210 --> 00:06:21,350
You do all the hard work too.

99
00:06:21,979 --> 00:06:23,478
You covered the windows
with mattresses yesterday...

100
00:06:23,479 --> 00:06:25,349
Do you think I did that
because I wanted to?

101
00:06:25,350 --> 00:06:27,631
When bullets were literally
flying in through the windows?

102
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,890
I did it
because you were about to do it.

103
00:06:30,359 --> 00:06:31,858
If I didn't,
you would've done it instead.

104
00:06:31,859 --> 00:06:34,530
- I get it. Stop nagging.
- "Stop nagging?"

105
00:06:34,590 --> 00:06:36,599
I'm saying this for your sake.

106
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,330
Wait, a patient has arrived.

107
00:06:39,999 --> 00:06:43,439
(Emergency Medical Center)

108
00:06:48,369 --> 00:06:49,679
The patient is 18,

109
00:06:49,710 --> 00:06:51,630
and he's been shot in the hand
and lower abdomen.

110
00:06:51,780 --> 00:06:52,879
He's been shot?

111
00:07:00,489 --> 00:07:01,819
Let's prepare for surgery
right away.

112
00:07:01,820 --> 00:07:03,820
Prepare plenty of blood
for transfusion.

113
00:07:07,530 --> 00:07:08,629
Darn it.

114
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,329
Those darn punks.

115
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:16,998
Now they're even shooting civilians
with the guns meant to protect them?

116
00:07:16,999 --> 00:07:18,799
Can you believe this?

117
00:07:20,169 --> 00:07:22,210
What did the kid do to deserve this?

118
00:07:27,450 --> 00:07:30,279
Jung Tae,
can't you come sleep at home?

119
00:07:30,280 --> 00:07:32,390
I can give you a ride
back and forth.

120
00:07:32,590 --> 00:07:34,219
I'm really okay.

121
00:07:34,220 --> 00:07:35,488
No one has gone home.

122
00:07:35,489 --> 00:07:36,619
They're all sleeping here.

123
00:07:38,289 --> 00:07:39,928
I'm just so worried.

124
00:07:39,929 --> 00:07:41,989
And your father may ask
to see you soon.

125
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:44,900
He never asks to see me.

126
00:07:47,330 --> 00:07:48,369
What?

127
00:07:50,669 --> 00:07:53,270
Anyway, I won't go.
I'm going to stay here.

128
00:07:58,979 --> 00:08:00,379
Yes, ma'am.

129
00:08:01,510 --> 00:08:03,020
Our training is being carried out...

130
00:08:03,080 --> 00:08:05,119
strictly within the training camp.

131
00:08:05,220 --> 00:08:07,020
No one is taking
a single step out of here.

132
00:08:07,119 --> 00:08:09,119
So don't worry about Jung Tae.

133
00:08:09,689 --> 00:08:12,390
Please call me if something happens.

134
00:08:12,660 --> 00:08:14,059
Yes, of course.

135
00:08:14,530 --> 00:08:15,999
Okay, goodbye.

136
00:08:20,929 --> 00:08:21,929
Yes?

137
00:08:22,869 --> 00:08:25,470
We're training strictly within
the training camp.

138
00:08:27,809 --> 00:08:29,079
(Emergency Room, Nurse's Station)

139
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:31,080
What did they say?
Is Myeong Soo okay?

140
00:08:32,410 --> 00:08:33,849
They're staying
strictly inside the training camp,

141
00:08:33,850 --> 00:08:34,979
so he said not to worry.

142
00:08:40,989 --> 00:08:42,789
If you're concerned,
shall we bring him here?

143
00:08:42,790 --> 00:08:43,790
I'll go get him.

144
00:08:44,619 --> 00:08:47,380
It's better for him to stay there
instead of seeing what goes on here.

145
00:08:48,229 --> 00:08:49,629
It's safer too.

146
00:08:57,999 --> 00:08:59,239
That punk.

147
00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:12,420
You think you're so darn fast?

148
00:09:18,859 --> 00:09:20,129
Are you crazy?

149
00:09:20,759 --> 00:09:22,659
Soo Gon, get out of here now!

150
00:09:23,330 --> 00:09:25,399
- You darn...
- Sergeant Hong!

151
00:09:26,869 --> 00:09:27,998
Don't come any closer!

152
00:09:27,999 --> 00:09:30,099
If you do, I'll kill this jerk!

153
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:32,508
You crazy punk.
Private Kim, what are you doing?

154
00:09:32,509 --> 00:09:34,869
Shoot him now! Shoot him!

155
00:09:37,710 --> 00:09:39,080
I'm going to kill you!

156
00:09:39,779 --> 00:09:41,180
Shoot him!

157
00:09:56,330 --> 00:09:58,076
Due to the military's excessive use
of force,

158
00:09:58,100 --> 00:10:00,769
hundreds of innocent civilians
have been injured.

159
00:10:01,229 --> 00:10:02,800
Someone even died yesterday.

160
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:06,238
We must make
the troops withdraw immediately.

161
00:10:06,239 --> 00:10:08,970
Withdrawing suddenly like this
won't solve anything.

162
00:10:09,879 --> 00:10:10,908
What?

163
00:10:10,909 --> 00:10:13,108
Do you think they were dispatched
for no reason?

164
00:10:13,109 --> 00:10:14,810
It's more important to suppress
the mob...

165
00:10:14,850 --> 00:10:16,420
that's causing this whole frenzy.

166
00:10:16,550 --> 00:10:19,789
Whose side are you on right now?

167
00:10:19,790 --> 00:10:22,290
We're gathered here
to sort this situation out.

168
00:10:22,519 --> 00:10:23,920
We're not here to take sides.

169
00:10:26,489 --> 00:10:29,229
Or perhaps, Father,

170
00:10:29,899 --> 00:10:32,999
are you here
to represent one side in particular?

171
00:10:33,769 --> 00:10:35,429
Please watch your mouth.

172
00:10:35,430 --> 00:10:37,499
You're the ones
who should watch your mouths.

173
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:39,408
- What? What did you say?
- Did I say something wrong?

174
00:10:39,409 --> 00:10:41,710
How could you say that
to an assemblyman?

175
00:10:42,940 --> 00:10:45,950
These are the minutes from
today's emergency committee meeting.

176
00:10:49,350 --> 00:10:53,119
Did you participate in the meeting
and write this yourself?

177
00:10:54,350 --> 00:10:55,350
No, sir.

178
00:10:55,619 --> 00:10:58,189
The officials who were present
at the meeting wrote them...

179
00:10:58,190 --> 00:10:59,259
Mr. Hwang.

180
00:10:59,930 --> 00:11:00,989
We are...

181
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:03,899
in positions
that require some legwork.

182
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:06,999
How will you control the situation
if you sit behind a desk...

183
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,470
and simply receive reports?

184
00:11:09,769 --> 00:11:10,940
This really...

185
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,570
troubles me.

186
00:11:14,170 --> 00:11:15,738
I mean it's safe to say
that the martial law...

187
00:11:15,739 --> 00:11:17,840
has been expanded
mainly because of Gwangju.

188
00:11:19,850 --> 00:11:22,580
I'll make sure to participate
in future meetings myself.

189
00:11:41,869 --> 00:11:43,239
You loaded the bullets backwards.

190
00:11:43,970 --> 00:11:46,169
- Did you do this on purpose?
- I'm sorry, sir.

191
00:11:46,170 --> 00:11:49,839
Hey. Did you join this place
to protect the commies?

192
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:52,109
How can you call yourself a soldier?

193
00:11:52,609 --> 00:11:54,450
Answer me, you punk.

194
00:11:55,210 --> 00:11:58,779
How dare you load your bullets
backwards?

195
00:11:59,119 --> 00:12:01,690
You stupid punk.
I can't believe you.

196
00:12:03,489 --> 00:12:04,889
You're a darn disgrace.

197
00:12:21,869 --> 00:12:22,940
Corporal Lee.

198
00:12:23,909 --> 00:12:25,810
I'm sorry
about what happened earlier.

199
00:12:27,450 --> 00:12:29,008
I just couldn't get myself
to shoot...

200
00:12:29,009 --> 00:12:31,009
Do you think I fired that shot
because I wanted to?

201
00:12:33,790 --> 00:12:35,019
Hey, Kim Kyung Soo.

202
00:12:35,749 --> 00:12:37,820
Do you think that makes you
a nice person?

203
00:12:41,159 --> 00:12:42,430
This is the army.

204
00:12:44,159 --> 00:12:45,859
If you don't shoot, I have to.

205
00:12:46,830 --> 00:12:48,069
Can you call yourself nice...

206
00:12:48,070 --> 00:12:50,390
if you force things on others
to keep your own hands clean?

207
00:12:51,340 --> 00:12:53,310
That's what you call being selfish.

208
00:12:54,869 --> 00:12:56,009
I'm sorry, sir.

209
00:13:01,979 --> 00:13:04,699
If you don't want to shoot anyone,
arrest them as quickly as you can,

210
00:13:06,249 --> 00:13:07,519
before someone else shoots.

211
00:13:25,300 --> 00:13:27,969
What on earth is that sound?
I've been hearing it all day.

212
00:13:27,970 --> 00:13:30,680
Don't worry. It's probably nothing.

213
00:13:30,779 --> 00:13:33,779
Chang Geun,
it's time to take your medicine.

214
00:13:37,479 --> 00:13:39,619
Did Soo Chan really go to work
this morning?

215
00:13:40,889 --> 00:13:41,920
Why?

216
00:13:42,249 --> 00:13:43,969
Is he not answering the phone
at the office?

217
00:13:44,420 --> 00:13:46,259
Did you actually see Soo Chan leave?

218
00:13:48,830 --> 00:13:50,430
Tell me. What is going on?

219
00:13:52,629 --> 00:13:53,769
Chang Geun.

220
00:13:54,670 --> 00:13:56,440
You need to calm down first.

221
00:13:56,600 --> 00:13:59,239
Tell me! What happened to Soo Chan?

222
00:14:14,889 --> 00:14:15,950
Sir.

223
00:14:16,859 --> 00:14:17,920
Sir.

224
00:14:19,690 --> 00:14:21,960
Over here. A person has collapsed.

225
00:14:22,590 --> 00:14:25,600
A man has collapsed. Please...

226
00:14:27,930 --> 00:14:30,499
- My gosh.
- Who told you to move?

227
00:14:30,899 --> 00:14:32,040
Do you want to die?

228
00:14:32,540 --> 00:14:33,909
Get back in your position.

229
00:14:37,479 --> 00:14:38,599
What are you all looking at?

230
00:14:39,350 --> 00:14:40,950
Eyes down!

231
00:14:43,850 --> 00:14:44,850
Take him away.

232
00:14:51,359 --> 00:14:52,359
Sir...

233
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:06,509
Hey. Get back in your position,
you punk.

234
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:12,950
What? Who was arrested?

235
00:15:13,979 --> 00:15:15,279
Soo Ryeon's older brother.

236
00:15:15,509 --> 00:15:17,119
I'm not sure,

237
00:15:17,220 --> 00:15:19,420
but can you check
if he's really been arrested?

238
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:21,119
What a hassle.

239
00:15:23,119 --> 00:15:24,290
Tell them I'll check.

240
00:15:26,090 --> 00:15:28,060
But what is going on?

241
00:15:28,259 --> 00:15:30,128
People are calling all day,
asking me to find people.

242
00:15:30,129 --> 00:15:31,430
There's no need for you to know.

243
00:15:31,529 --> 00:15:33,100
Just keep to the house for now.

244
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:39,840
By the way...

245
00:15:47,810 --> 00:15:49,149
Has Hee Tae called?

246
00:15:52,379 --> 00:15:53,519
No.

247
00:15:55,619 --> 00:15:57,220
You should check on him first.

248
00:15:58,060 --> 00:16:00,620
Don't sit back and do nothing
just because he doesn't call first.

249
00:16:02,460 --> 00:16:04,129
He never asks to see me.

250
00:16:08,869 --> 00:16:10,570
Why aren't you asking
about Jung Tae?

251
00:16:12,840 --> 00:16:14,520
Why are you asking me that
out of the blue?

252
00:16:15,570 --> 00:16:17,909
Jung Tae is your son too.

253
00:16:18,310 --> 00:16:21,450
You haven't seen him in days.
Aren't you worried about him?

254
00:16:21,950 --> 00:16:24,149
Do you think I have the time
to worry about the kid?

255
00:16:24,279 --> 00:16:26,239
That's enough of your nonsense.
Just give me that.

256
00:16:38,999 --> 00:16:40,869
I finally got in touch with Mr. Lee.

257
00:16:41,769 --> 00:16:44,700
He'll be here early in the morning.

258
00:16:47,139 --> 00:16:48,769
That's a relief.

259
00:16:51,909 --> 00:16:55,310
Once he gets here,
let's leave immediately.

260
00:16:57,680 --> 00:16:58,979
Immediately?

261
00:17:00,489 --> 00:17:04,220
Our plan was to stay here
until Mr. Lee comes to get Jin A.

262
00:17:09,500 --> 00:17:11,530
What's with that face?

263
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:15,030
It's not like that.

264
00:17:15,770 --> 00:17:17,469
Then what is it?

265
00:17:17,899 --> 00:17:19,869
If something is bothering you,
just tell me.

266
00:17:20,969 --> 00:17:22,609
It's just that...

267
00:17:23,409 --> 00:17:24,939
if we leave,

268
00:17:25,639 --> 00:17:28,080
the others will have to do
more work.

269
00:17:29,409 --> 00:17:31,080
That's what I was worried about.

270
00:17:36,990 --> 00:17:40,629
What? Were you thinking
that I'm a pushover?

271
00:17:43,899 --> 00:17:45,500
No way.

272
00:17:46,199 --> 00:17:48,100
I was thinking
you are such a good person.

273
00:17:50,939 --> 00:17:52,469
But listen, Myeong Hee.

274
00:17:53,570 --> 00:17:56,040
If you really want to be good,
you must put yourself first.

275
00:17:56,679 --> 00:17:59,109
If you put others before yourself,

276
00:17:59,850 --> 00:18:01,810
that's hypocrisy, I think.

277
00:18:03,280 --> 00:18:05,780
Don't people normally call that
a sacrifice?

278
00:18:07,290 --> 00:18:09,659
They would normally.

279
00:18:10,790 --> 00:18:11,990
But...

280
00:18:12,929 --> 00:18:15,459
to someone who loves you,
it's hypocrisy.

281
00:18:19,359 --> 00:18:23,340
So for now,
let's put you and me first.

282
00:18:33,709 --> 00:18:35,979
We'll be training indoors
again today.

283
00:18:35,980 --> 00:18:38,179
Get ready and come out
as quickly as you can.

284
00:18:42,490 --> 00:18:44,820
Gosh, I feel so cooped up.

285
00:18:45,020 --> 00:18:47,530
Why can't we go out?

286
00:18:48,429 --> 00:18:50,800
It's my birthday today,
and I'm stuck indoors all day.

287
00:18:50,859 --> 00:18:54,330
Oh, my.
Is it your birthday today, Sung Il?

288
00:18:54,469 --> 00:18:56,939
Gosh, then we should celebrate.

289
00:18:57,340 --> 00:18:59,609
You said
you love comic books, right?

290
00:18:59,770 --> 00:19:01,270
Should we go borrow some comics?

291
00:19:01,469 --> 00:19:04,439
If we can't even train outside,
how can we go to the rental store?

292
00:19:04,580 --> 00:19:07,849
My gosh.
We have two fast runners here.

293
00:19:07,850 --> 00:19:09,570
You two can rush over there
and borrow some.

294
00:19:09,649 --> 00:19:12,480
Gather around. I have a plan.

295
00:19:18,419 --> 00:19:20,260
I'm going grocery shopping.

296
00:19:20,790 --> 00:19:22,159
See you.

297
00:19:33,609 --> 00:19:35,369
Excuse me, Coach.

298
00:19:35,609 --> 00:19:39,280
Do you have any digestive medicine?

299
00:19:39,409 --> 00:19:41,479
I think I have an upset stomach.

300
00:19:41,480 --> 00:19:44,719
You have an upset stomach?
You, Jin Kyu?

301
00:19:45,649 --> 00:19:48,050
- Then let me prick your fingers.
- What?

302
00:19:49,859 --> 00:19:52,459
I think some medicine will do.

303
00:19:52,689 --> 00:19:54,589
Medicine won't do any good.

304
00:19:54,590 --> 00:19:56,959
Pricking all ten fingers
is the best remedy.

305
00:20:33,530 --> 00:20:34,899
You still can't reach them?

306
00:20:35,469 --> 00:20:37,839
You can't make
any long-distance calls?

307
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:39,540
It's just Gwangju
that's out of reach.

308
00:20:41,409 --> 00:20:44,179
This won't do
I'll have to go there myself.

309
00:20:44,980 --> 00:20:46,750
Go where? To Gwangju?

310
00:20:47,109 --> 00:20:48,879
By yourself?

311
00:20:49,179 --> 00:20:52,320
I've heard some terrible rumors.

312
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:54,290
That's why I should go there.

313
00:20:55,020 --> 00:20:57,520
(From Kim Hyun Chul,
To Kim Myeong Hee)

314
00:20:59,990 --> 00:21:02,030
I hope everything's fine.

315
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:07,398
Hyun Chul, where are you going?

316
00:21:07,399 --> 00:21:10,269
Mother, I have to make
a quick trip to Gwangju.

317
00:21:10,270 --> 00:21:14,570
Don't go. Stay with me.

318
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:18,780
Mother, have a seat for a second.

319
00:21:20,449 --> 00:21:24,279
I'll come back as soon as I know
the kids are fine.

320
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,379
Don't worry and stay put, okay?

321
00:21:31,919 --> 00:21:36,500
My goodness,
you look so beautiful, Mother.

322
00:21:42,030 --> 00:21:43,540
See you later.

323
00:21:44,639 --> 00:21:46,039
You don't have to come out.

324
00:21:46,040 --> 00:21:48,669
- Be careful.
- Don't worry.

325
00:22:00,119 --> 00:22:02,918
Hey, let's get a box
of Choco Pies too.

326
00:22:02,919 --> 00:22:04,118
We'll pretend it's a cake.

327
00:22:04,119 --> 00:22:06,689
Is it your birthday?
You're not the one paying...

328
00:22:20,909 --> 00:22:24,378
My goodness. You should stop.

329
00:22:24,379 --> 00:22:27,409
What if the man dies or something?
You're going too far.

330
00:22:28,050 --> 00:22:30,149
Round up everyone here!

331
